                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-29T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 29, 1922—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>160. Department’s No. 92 of April 20, 4 p.m.<note n="69" xml:id="d505fn69">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Italian Government having acquiesced this government is instructing its
                    representatives at London, Paris, Tokyo, Rome, Brussels, The Hague and Lisbon,
                    to approach the Governments to which they are respectively accredited with the
                    request that they each now indicate their formal approval of the resolution in
                    amended form (see page 737 of Senate Document 126<note n="70" xml:id="d505fn70"
                        >67th Cong., 2d sess.</note>) which was offered during the Conference on
                    Limitation of Armaments at Washington. You will inform those of your colleagues
                    who represent powers which participated in the Conference of this action on the
                    part of this Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
